Two distinctly different categories of nematocysts were observed in hydroids of this species, with the larger of the two appearing to occur in two somewhat different forms (
Fig. 11
). They appear to correspond with A-type b-mastigophores (5.5–6.4 μm long x 1.2–1.5 μm wide, undischarged, n=10, ROMIZ B4369) and B-type b-mas- tigophores (7.0–8.0 long x 1.6–2.2 μm wide, undischarged, n=10, ROMIZ B4369).

